              <div class="accordion" id="faqAccordion" style="--bs-accordion-border-color: #c8ff00; --bs-accordion-btn-color: #c8ff00; --bs-accordion-active-color: #c8ff00; --bs-accordion-btn-focus-box-shadow: 0 0 0 0.25rem rgba(200, 255, 0, 0.25);">
                <!-- Question 1 -->
                <div class="accordion-item mb-3" data-aos="fade-up" style="background-color: #1b1b1b; border-color: #c8ff00;">
                  <h2 class="accordion-header">
                    <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq1" style="background-color: #1b1b1b; color: #c8ff00;">
                      How do I report a security vulnerability?
                    </button>
                  </h2>
                  <div id="faq1" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                    <div class="accordion-body" style="background-color: #1b1b1b; color: #ffffffbd;">
                        <p>For security vulnerabilities, please email <strong>security@cipherheist.com</strong> with detailed information about the issue. We strongly encourage using our <a href="pgp-key.html" style="color: #c8ff00; text-decoration: none;">PGP key</a> for encrypted communication when reporting sensitive security matters.</p>
                        <p>Include steps to reproduce, affected versions, and any proof-of-concept code. We aim to respond to all vulnerability reports within 48 hours.</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                
                <!-- Question 2 -->
                <div class="accordion-item mb-3" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100" style="background-color: #1b1b1b; border-color: #c8ff00;">
                  <h2 class="accordion-header">
                    <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq2" style="background-color: #1b1b1b; color: #c8ff00;">
                      Are your security tools really free?
                    </button>
                  </h2>
                  <div id="faq2" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                    <div class="accordion-body" style="background-color: #1b1b1b; color: #ffffffbd;">
                     <p>Yes, all tools available on Cipher Heist are completely free to download and use. We believe in making cybersecurity tools accessible to everyone.</p>
                     <p>Some of our tools are open-source under MIT License, while others are freeware. We may offer premium     support or enterprise versions in the future, but the core functionality will always remain free.</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                
                <!-- Question 3 -->
                <div class="accordion-item mb-3" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="200" style="background-color: #1b1b1b; border-color: #c8ff00;">
                  <h2 class="accordion-header">
                    <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq3" style="background-color: #1b1b1b; color: #c8ff00;">
                      Can I contribute to your open-source projects?
                    </button>
                  </h2>
                  <div id="faq3" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                    <div class="accordion-body" style="background-color: #1b1b1b; color: #ffffffbd;">
                      <p>Absolutely! We welcome contributions from the security community. Visit our <a href="https://github.com/cipherheist" style="color: #c8ff00; text-decoration: none;">GitHub repository</a> to view open issues, feature requests, and contribution guidelines.</p>
                        <p>Before submitting major changes, please open an issue to discuss your proposed modifications. All contributors must agree to our code of conduct and sign a contributor license agreement.</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
                
                <!-- Question 4 -->
                <div class="accordion-item mb-3" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="300" style="background-color: #1b1b1b; border-color: #c8ff00;">
                  <h2 class="accordion-header">
                    <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq4" style="background-color: #1b1b1b; color: #c8ff00;">
                      How can I verify the integrity of downloaded tools?
                    </button>
                  </h2>
                  <div id="faq4" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
                    <div class="accordion-body" style="background-color: #1b1b1b; color: #ffffff9d;">
                    <p>We provide SHA-256 checksums and PGP signatures for all downloadable tools. These can be found on each tool's download page.</p>
                    <p>To verify a PGP signature:</p>
                    <ol>
                    <li>Import our public key: <code style="color: #c8ff00; background: #121212;">gpg --recv-keys 0xABCDEF123456</code></li>
                    <li>Verify the signature: <code style="color: #c8ff00; background: #121212;">gpg --verify toolname.sig toolname.exe</code></li>
                    </ol>
                    <p>Always verify downloads before executing them, especially security tools.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
    
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
      </div>
